#Text=Malaysia says debris found in Maldives could be from MH370
#Text=Wednesday , August 12 , 2015
#Text=Photo of suspected plane debris that washed ashore the Maldive Kaafu Atoll on May 31 .
#Text=Image : Mohamed Wafir ( via Facebook ) .
#Text=This map displays the location of Reunion Island , because of the debris part found there in 2015-07 , in relation to the known flight path of Malaysia Airlines Flight 370 .
#Text=Image : AHeneen .
#Text=Malaysian
#Text=officials stated Wednesday , some of the debris found in the Maldives will be brought back to Malaysia to determine if they are from Malaysia Airlines Flight 370 ( MH370 ) as they now believe .
#Text=A team arrived Tuesday in Maldives to take charge of the debris , which had previously been disposed of as trash .

#Text=" We [ Malaysia ] have an understanding with the authorities there [ Maldives ] ... we think the parts which were found about a month ago were parts of the aircraft , " said Ab Aziz Kaprawi , the deputy transport minister for Malaysia as quoted by Bernama , a Malaysian government news agency .
#Text=" They have to be further analysed and will be brought back to Malaysia for verification , " he added .
#Text="

#Text=The parts are currently undergoing few processes before they can be released and brought to Malaysia for further identification and verification ,  said Seri Liow Tiong Lai , Malaysia 's transport minister during a press conference today .

column1: #Text=Malaysia 's Department of Civil Aviation will be in charge of examining the debris once it arrives in the country .
#Text=The debris washed ashore the Kaafu Atoll reportedly around May 31 and was recovered by employees of the Banyan Tree Vabbinfaru Resort .
#Text=However the debris had been disposed of as trash before authorities could examine it .
#Text=An investigation into the debris was launched after photos of it were uploaded to the social networking service Facebook , by an employee of the resort .
#Text=The photographs show a large white object , possibly two , stained with algae and appear to be made of a fiberglass and honeycomb material .
#Text=Debris has since washed ashore on at least three other Maldives locations , the Baa Atoll , and the islands of Fehendhoo and Fulhahdhoo , but most of it is n't believed to be from an aircraft .
#Text=Abdulla Rasheed , a captain of a cargo boat which recently capsized in the waters off the Maldives stated , "

#Text= We are collecting any unidentified debris and storing them in a warehouse so that the Malaysians can carry out tests and determine if it is from their plane or not , " said the office of the Maldives President in a statement reported by Haveeru Daily on Monday .

column1: #Text=MH370 , while flying from Kuala Lumpur , Malaysia to Beijing , China , vanished on March 8 , 2014 .
#Text=All 239 passengers and crew are believed to be dead .
#Text=On the day the plane went missing , residents on the small Maldives island of Kudahuvadhoo claimed to have seen a very " low flying jumbo jet " crash into the Indian Ocean .
#Text=Some also noted the colors appeared to resemble that of a Malaysia Airlines plane .
#Text=" I ’ve never seen a jet flying so low over our island before .
